Philip Morris International Inc. (PM) ,
the worldâ€™s largest publicly traded tobacco company, said the
cigarette market in the  Czech Republic  fell 2.9 percent in the
first quarter.  The market share of Philip Morris brands declined 1.4
percentage points to 43.6 percent and it shipped 6 percent fewer
cigarettes in the period as demand for labels like Petra or
Sparta fell, the company said in a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
